@REMARK------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "Intro" "Introduction"
@NEXT "Require"

@{CODE}@{JCENTER}@{APEN 2}Introduction
@{JLEFT}@{APEN 1}
@{BODY}MagicWB Stuff 6 is a collection of icons, patterns and other stuff which I make
for everyone to enjoy. All I ask is that you @{"send a postcard to Roman Patzner" LINK "Card"}
and @{"email me" LINK "Author"} to let me know what you think of this archive. All included icons
and patterns follow the MWB standards (if they exist under the circumstances).
@{PAR}
@{PAR}The original archive should contain the following (as well, some files may
have associated icons):
@{PAR}@{CODE}
@{" Icons    (dir) " LINK "Icons"}
@{" Misc     (dir) " LINK "Misc"}
@{" MUI      (dir) " LINK "MUIDrawer"}
@{" P&C      (dir) " LINK "P&C"}
@{" Patterns (dir) " LINK "Patterns"}
@{" S        (dir) " LINK "S"}
@{" TrevsDB       " SYSTEM "SYS:Utilities/MultiView TrevsDB"} - a snapshot of my WB
@{" SYSOPS.README " SYSTEM "SYS:Utilities/MultiView SYSOPS.README"} - a note to sysops
@{" Stuff6.guide  " LINK ""} - you're reading it @{APEN 2}@{B}:@{UB}@{APEN 1}-)

@{B}NOTE TO SYSOPS:@{UB} If anything is missing/added from/to the above list, please
delete the archive from your BBS (my intent is NOT to spread any viruses).
Also, please read the @{"SYSOPS.README" SYSTEM "SYS:Utilities/MultiView SYSOPS.README"}...Thanx!!

@ENDNODE

@REMARK------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "P&C" "Pointer & Color (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "Intro"
@TOC "Intro"

@{CODE}@{JCENTER}@{APEN 2}Pointer & Color

@{JLEFT}@{APEN 1}@{BODY}The P&C drawer should contain the following (as well, some files may have
associated icons):
@{PAR}@{CODE}
ClickForColors16 - Changes the palette to 16 colors (MWB).
ClickForColors8  - Changes the palette to 8 colors (MWB).
ClickForPointer  - Changes your pointer to look like mine.
ClickMeFirst     - Executes MagicWB-Demon (for correct 8 & 16 color palette).
                   (You need to register @{"MWB2.0" LINK "MWB"} to get MagicWB-Demon).
ClickMeForScreen - This will launch the ScreenPrefs util. If you want a 16 color
                   MWB, just slide the colors to 16; if you an 8 color MWB,
                   slide it to 8 colors and hit @{B}USE@{UB}.

@{BODY}This drawer contains my palette and pointer prefs. Double-Clicking on their
icons will only change your prefs until you reboot. If you wish to permanently
save these prefs, double-click on the icons and then load the appropriate prefs
util from your sys:prefs/ drawer (either PointerPrefs or PalettePrefs) and then
click on @{B}SAVE@{UB}. See @{"About the MWB16 Icons" LINK "16Icons"}.

@ENDNODE

@REMARK------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "S" "S (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "Intro"
@TOC "Intro"

@{CODE}@{JCENTER}@{APEN 2}S (dir)

@{JLEFT}@{APEN 1}The S drawer should contain the following:

Randomizer - a sample line for your startup-sequence (or user-startup)
             randomize your patterns using @{"FilePick by Simon Brown" LINK "FP"}.
Shell-Startup - my shell start-up (rename yours and try this one out).
AddMeToYourS-S - a sample line for 16 color MWB - See @{"About the MWB16 Icons" LINK "16Icons"}.

@ENDNODE

@REMARK------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "MUIDrawer" "MUI (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "Intro"
@TOC "Intro"

@{CODE}@{JCENTER}@{APEN 2}MUI (dir)

@{JLEFT}@{APEN 1}@{BODY}The MUI/Images/Trevor/Gradient/8/ drawer should contain the
following images:
@{PAR}@{CODE}
ArrowDown.mf0     ArrowDown.mf1
ArrowLeft.mf0     ArrowLeft.mf1
ArrowRight.mf0    ArrowRight.mf1
ArrowUp.mf0       ArrowUp.mf1
CheckMark.mf0     CheckMark.mf1
Cycle.mbr         PopDrawer.mf0
PopDrawer.mf1     PopFile.mf0
PopFile.mf1       PopUp.mf0
PopUp.mf1         RadioButton.mf0
RadioButton.mf1

@{BODY}The CycleGad was copied from the included WD set, but I shortened it for
inclusion in my set.
@{PAR}
@{PAR}These are just some small images I drew for @{"MUI" LINK "MUI"} because I found that all the
other ones were to large. Copy them into your MUI drawer (The path follows the
@{"MUI3+" LINK "MUI"} convention - people using less than version 3 will have to alter the path
slightly).
@{PAR}
@{PAR}A Template is included in the @{"Misc (dir)" LINK "Misc"}.

@ENDNODE

@REMARK------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "Misc" "Misc (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "Intro"
@TOC "Intro"

@{CODE}@{JCENTER}@{APEN 2}Misc (dir)

@{JLEFT}@{APEN 1}@{BODY}The Misc drawer should contain the following (as well, some files may have
associated icons):
@{PAR}@{CODE}
@{" MUI_Template " SYSTEM "SYS:Utilities/MultiView misc/MUI_Template"}
@{" MWB_Template " SYSTEM "SYS:Utilities/MultiView misc/MWB_Template"}
@{" MWB16Icons   " SYSTEM "SYS:Utilities/MultiView misc/MWB16Icons"}

@{BODY}The Templates may be used to create your own icons and buttons. They contain
all icon standards of which I am currently aware (let @{"me" LINK "Author"} know if you find any
that are missing).

@ENDNODE

@REMARK------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "Icons" "Icons (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "Intro"
@TOC "Intro"

@{CODE}@{JCENTER}@{APEN 2}Icons (dir)

@{JLEFT}@{APEN 1}The Icons drawer should contain the following:

@{"16_Color  (dir)" LINK "Icons2" 5}
@{"Def_Icons (dir)" LINK "Icons2" 39}
@{"DOpus5    (dir)" LINK "Icons2" 42}
@{"NewIcons  (dir)" LINK "Icons2" 79}
